def execute_command(system, tools):
    # Use dataset exemplars to get an initial set of images that highly activate the neuron
    activation_list, image_list = tools.dataset_exemplars(system)
    # Summarize the common visual elements in these images
    image_summary = tools.summarize_images(image_list)
    # Log the experiment
    tools.save_experiment_log(activation_list, image_list, [f"dataset exemplars {i+1}" for i in range(len(activation_list))], image_summary)

def execute_command(system, tools):
    # Test hypothesis that the neuron is selective for the presence of women
    prompts_women = ["a woman smiling in a park", "a woman running on a track", "a group of women in a meeting"]
    prompts_men = ["a man smiling in a park", "a man running on a track", "a group of men in a meeting"]
    # Generate images based on these prompts
    images_women = tools.text2image(prompts_women)
    images_men = tools.text2image(prompts_men)
    # Measure neuron activation for these images
    activation_list_women, activation_map_list_women = system.call_neuron(images_women)
    activation_list_men, activation_map_list_men = system.call_neuron(images_men)
    # Describe the images to ensure they are being generated as expected (e.g., they include women or men)
    descriptions_women = tools.describe_images(activation_map_list_women, prompts_women)
    descriptions_men = tools.describe_images(activation_map_list_men, prompts_men)
    # Save experiment log
    tools.save_experiment_log(activation_list_women + activation_list_men, activation_map_list_women + activation_map_list_men, prompts_women + prompts_men, descriptions_women + descriptions_men)
```

def execute_command(system, tools):
    # Test the influence of attire and grouping on neuron activation
    # Create prompts for women in different attire and group settings
    prompts_detailed_women = [
        "a woman in business attire sitting at a table with documents",
        "a group of women wearing athletic clothing and running together",
        "two women in casual clothing smiling together in a park"
    ]
    # Create prompts for men in similar settings
    prompts_detailed_men = [
        "a man in business attire sitting at a table with documents",
        "a group of men wearing athletic clothing and running together",
        "two men in casual clothing smiling together in a park"
    ]
    
    # Generate images based on these prompts
    images_detailed_women = tools.text2image(prompts_detailed_women)
    images_detailed_men = tools.text2image(prompts_detailed_men)
    
    # Measure neuron activation for these images
    activation_list_detailed_women, activation_map_list_detailed_women = system.call_neuron(images_detailed_women)
    activation_list_detailed_men, activation_map_list_detailed_men = system.call_neuron(images_detailed_men)
    
    # Describe the images to confirm the contents and attire
    descriptions_detailed_women = tools.describe_images(activation_map_list_detailed_women, prompts_detailed_women)
    descriptions_detailed_men = tools.describe_images(activation_map_list_detailed_men, prompts_detailed_men)
    
    # Save experiment log
    tools.save_experiment_log(
        activation_list_detailed_women + activation_list_detailed_men,
        activation_map_list_detailed_women + activation_map_list_detailed_men,
        prompts_detailed_women + prompts_detailed_men,
        descriptions_detailed_women + descriptions_detailed_men
    )
```
